==English==

===Etymology===
Coined by Theodore Seuss "Dr. Seuss" Giesel in ''The Lorax'' (ISBN 0394823370)

===Noun===
'''thneed'''

# A multi-purpose object [[knit]]ted from the [[tuft]]s of the [[w:The Lorax|truffula tree]].

===Quotation===
*'''1978''' ''However, for people who have not read The Lorax, thneed is a nonsense syllable which does not quite conform to English syllable structure rules.'' &mdash; John Higgins in ''Bulletin of the Language Association of Thailand''